    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-03-26T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-03-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="160"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d160">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11G93/1089: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-26T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 26, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Consul Guayaquil cables officials refuse to furnish him information regarding
                    daily deposits. After communicating with Consul request Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs for explanation of refusal.</p>
                <pb facs="0287" n="197" xml:id="pg_197"/>
                <p>If daily deposits do not amount to sum provided for in 1908 agreement,<note
                        n="21" xml:id="d160fn21">For correspondence concerning 1908 agreement, see
                            <ref target="frus1908#pg_273">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1908, pp. 273</ref> ff.</note>
                    inquire reason of Foreign Office. Cable report:</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
